19
00:01:08,440 --> 00:01:11,020
What we generally start
with the hardware

20
00:01:11,020 --> 00:01:14,150
run the operating system on
that device that we have.

21
00:01:14,150 --> 00:01:19,120
And the applications that we directly
deal with, that we run on our systems,

22
00:01:19,120 --> 00:01:25,030
so this could be your browser, let's
say, or this could be your mail client.

23
00:01:25,030 --> 00:01:29,160
So these applications then actually
running on top of the operating system.

24
00:01:29,160 --> 00:01:33,420
One way to think about this picture
